<p>Circular Segment Equation and Calculator </p>
<p>Circular segment is a region of a circle which is "cut off" from the res=
t of the circle by a secant or a chord . More formally, a circular segment =
is a region of two-dimensional space that is bounded by an arc (of less tha=
n 180=C2=B0) of a circle and by the chord connecting the endpoints of the a=
rc. </p>
<p><img src=3D"https://www.engineersedge.com/math/images/circle-segment.png=
" alt=3D"Chord Length" width=3D"262" height=3D"262"></p>
<p>Where:</p>
<p><em><strong>Radius:</strong></em></p>
<p>R =3D h + d =3D h / 2 + c<sup>2</sup> / ( 8h ) </p>
<p><em><strong>Arc Length:</strong></em></p>
<p>s =3D arcsin ( c / ( h + c<sup>2</sup> / 4h ) ) ( h + c<sup>2</sup> / 4h=
 ) </p>
<p><em><strong>Chord Length:  <strong>=CE=B8</strong> given in radians.</st=
rong></em></p>
<p>c =3D 2 R sin ( =CE=B8 / 2 ) </p>
<p><em><strong>Angle</strong></em>:</p>
<p>=CE=B8 =3D 2 arctan ( c / ( 2 d ) )</p>
<p><em><strong> Sagitta:  <strong>=CE=B8</strong> given in radians.</strong=
></em></p>
<p>h =3D R ( 1 - cos ( <strong>=CE=B8</strong> / 2) )</p>
<p><em><strong>Area: </strong></em></p>
<p>The area A of the circular segment is equal to the area of the circular =
sector minus the area of the triangular portion. <strong>=CE=B8</strong> gi=
ven in radians. </p>
<p><strong>A =3D (R<sup>2</sup> / 2 ) ( =CE=B8 - sin=CE=B8 )</strong></p>
<p>Central angle in radians </p>
<p><strong>A =3D ( R<sup>2</sup> / 2 ) ( ( =CE=B1 =CE=A0 )  / 180=C2=B0 - s=
in=CE=B8 )</strong> </p>
<p>Central angle in degrees </p>

